Here's an example JSON object for the user onboarding workflow:

```json
{
  "id": "onboarding-flow",
  "name": "Onboarding Workflow",
  "type": "action",
  "config": {
    "actions": [
      {
        "id": "user-1",
        "name": "Create User Account",
        "type": "condition",
        "config": {
          "condition": "user.email !== user.email_hash",
          "next": "user-2"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "user-2",
        "name": "Complete Registration",
        "type": "action",
        "config": {
          "next": "user-3"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "user-3",
        "name": "Set User Password",
        "type": "condition",
        "config": {
          "condition": "user.email_hash !== user.password_hash",
          "next": "user-4"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "user-4",
        "name": "Confirm User Password",
        "type": "action",
        "config": {
          "next": "user-5"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "user-5",
        "name": "Complete Password Reset",
        "type": "action",
        "config": {
          "next": null
        }
      }
    ],
    "conditions": [
      {
        "id": "user-1-condition",
        "name": "user.email_hash !== user.password_hash",
        "type": "condition",
        "config": {}
      },
      {
        "id": "user-2-condition",
        "name": "user.email !== user.email_hash",
        "type": "condition",
        "config": {}
      }
    ],
    "loops": [
      {
        "id": "user-1-loop",
        "name": "user-1",
        "type": "loop",
        "config": {
          "max": 10,
          "steps": [
            {
              "id": "user-1-step-1",
              "name": "user.email_hash",
              "type": "action",
              "config": {
                "action": "user.email_hash = random(5, 10)"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "user-1-step-2",
              "name": "user.password_hash",
              "type": "action",
              "config": {
                "action": "user.password_hash = random(5, 10)"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "user-2-loop",
        "name": "user-2",
        "type": "loop",
        "config": {
          "max": 5,
          "steps": [
            {
              "id": "user-2-step-1",
              "name": "user.email",
              "type": "action",
              "config": {
                "action": "user.email = random(10, 20)"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "user-2-step-2",
              "name": "user.password",
              "type": "action",
              "config": {
                "action": "user.password = random(10, 20)"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Note that the `config` and `next` properties are optional. The `config` is a nested object that contains the condition(s) to be applied to each step. The `next` property is a string or null, indicating the next step in the flow or skipping it altogether.

