Here's a sample JSON object representing a permission role hierarchy hierarchy:

```json
{
  "name": "Administrator",
  "id": 1,
  "children": [
    {
      "name": "Site Administrator",
      "id": 2,
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "Site Editor",
          "id": 3,
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Site Manager",
          "id": 4,
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "User Administrator",
      "id": 5,
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "User Editor",
          "id": 6,
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "name": "User Manager",
          "id": 7,
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Here's how to generate the JSON object from the above structure:

1. Create a nested array of objects representing each level of the hierarchy:
   ```javascript
   const levels = [
     {
       name: "Administrator",
       id: 1,
       children: [
         {
           name: "Site Administrator",
           id: 2,
           children: [
             {
               name: "Site Editor",
               id: 3,
               children: []
             },
             {
               name: "Site Manager",
               id: 4,
               children: []
             }
           ]
         },
         {
           name: "User Administrator",
           id: 5,
           children: [
             {
               name: "User Editor",
               id: 6,
               children: []
             },
             {
               name: "User Manager",
               id: 7,
               children: []
             }
           ]
         }
       ]
     }
   ];
   ```

2. Create a nested array of objects representing each level of the hierarchy:
   ```javascript
   const subobjects = levels.map(level => {
     const subobject = {
       name: level.name,
       id: level.id,
       children: level.children
     };
     return subobject;
   });
   ```

3. Create a nested array of objects representing each level of the hierarchy:
   ```javascript
   const result = subobjects.map(subobject => {
     const subobjectWithChildren = {
       ...subobject,
       children: subobject.children.map(child => {
         return {
           name: child.name,
           id: child.id,
           children: child.children
         };
       })
     };
     return subobjectWithChildren;
   });
   ```

4. Convert the nested array of objects into a nested array of arrays:
   ```javascript
   const result = result.map(subobject => {
     const subobjectWithChildren = subobject.children.map(child => {
       return {
         ...child,
         children: child.children
       };
     });
     return subobjectWithChildren;
   });
   ```

5. Convert the nested array of arrays into a nested array of objects:
   ```javascript
   const result = result.map(subobjectWithChildren => {
     const subobject = {
       ...subobjectWithChildren[0],
       id: subobjectWithChildren[0].id
     };
     return subobject;
   });
   ```

6. Convert the nested array of objects back into a JSON object:
   ```javascript
   const result = result.map(subobject => {
     return {
       name: subobject.name,
       id: subobject.id,
       children: subobject.children
     };
   });
   ```

With these steps, you should be able to generate the JSON object with nested arrays representing each level of the hierarchy hierarchy.

